In this example, we have a `MyService` class with a `doSomething()` method. We want to add a logging aspect to this method using Spring AOP.

We create a new aspect class `LoggingAspect` that will be applied to the `MyService` class. In this aspect, we use the `@Before` annotation to specify that the `log()` method should be executed before the `myMethod()` method in the target class.

