To enable AOP, we need to add the `@EnableAspectJAutoProxy` annotation to our main application class. This annotation tells Spring to enable auto-proxying for aspects.

Finally, we need to add the `@Aspect` annotation to our aspect class to indicate that it is an aspect.

With these configurations, the logging aspect will be applied to the `MyService` class, and the `log()` method will be called before the `doSomething()` method is executed.

